rComments: Kaija was an amazing writing teacher. Although the book we read was dry, she was so helpful in understanding the text and taking a stance in papers. She was there to give you advice on writing whenever you needed it and gave great feedback. If you want to become a better writer, definitely take her class.

Absolutely fabulous teacher, I found her exactly on point and thought that she made a hard subject very easy.  I had just failed the quarter previous, so it was nice to have a good teacher who could lay it out for me.
She makes mistakes all of the time.  She's not that hard but the class isn't very easy.  Don't take the class unless you have to.

Kaija is such a nice easygoing lady who wants you to learn and understand logic as much as possible. The only con I would say is that her lectures were jumbled and unclear. However, she's very helpful during office hours and through email. Tests are easy, overall if you are planning on taking logic at UCSC, Kaija's the one the best one to choose.
